<eesti>Politseiteenistusse v&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Employment in Police Service </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametnikule esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnikuna v&otilde;ib teenistusse v&otilde;tta 19-aastaseks saanud v&auml;hemalt keskharidusega Eesti kodaniku, kes valdab eesti keelt seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel antud &otilde;igusaktiga kehtestatud ulatuses ning vastab politseiametniku kutsesobivuse n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An Estonian citizen who has attained 19 years of age, has at least secondary education, is proficient in Estonian to the extent established by law or legislation issued on the basis of an Act and meets the professional requirements for police officers may be employed in the service as a police officer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametnike kutsesobivuse, sealhulgas f&uuml;&uuml;silise ettevalmistuse, haridus- ja tervisen&otilde;uded kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The professional requirements for police officers, including requirements for their physical training, educational background and health shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikud, keda on keelatud v&otilde;tta politseiteenistusse </eesti>
<inglise>Persons who shall not be employed in police service </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiteenistusse on keelatud v&otilde;tta isikut: </eesti>
<inglise>The following shall not be employed in the police service: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kes on teov&otilde;imetu v&otilde;i piiratud teov&otilde;imega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a person who has no active legal capacity or has restricted active legal capacity; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kellel on t&auml;itmata ajateenistuse kohustus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a person who has not undergone compulsory military service; </inglise>
<eesti>3) keda on karistatud tahtlikult toimepandud kuriteo eest; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a person who has been punished for an intentionally committed criminal offence; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kes on kandnud vabadusekaotuslikku karistust; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a person who has been convicted with a sentence of imprisonment; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kes on kriminaalasjas kahtlustatav, s&uuml;&uuml;distatav v&otilde;i kohtualune; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a person who is a suspect, the accused or accused at trial in a criminal case; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kellelt on j&otilde;ustunud kohtuotsusega &auml;ra v&otilde;etud politseiametniku ametikohal t&ouml;&ouml;tamise &otilde;igus; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a person deprived of the right to work in the position of police officer by a court judgment entered into force; </inglise>
<eesti>7) kes on l&auml;hedases suguluses (vanemad, vennad, &otilde;ed, lapsed) v&otilde;i h&otilde;imluses (abikaasa, abikaasa vanemad, vennad, &otilde;ed, lapsed) vastavat ametikohta vahetult kontrolliva ametniku v&otilde;i vahetu &uuml;lemusega; </eesti>
<inglise>7) persons closely related by blood (parents, brothers, sisters, children) or by marriage (spouse, spouse's parents, brothers, sisters, children) to an officer or the immediate superior who has direct control over the corresponding position; </inglise>
<eesti>8) kes saab v&auml;lisriigilt pensioni, t&ouml;&ouml;tasu v&otilde;i muid regulaarseid h&uuml;vitisi. </eesti>
<inglise>8) persons who receive a pension, remuneration or other regular benefits from a foreign state. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseivanne </eesti>
<inglise>Police oath </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiteenistusse astudes annab politseiametnik politseivande: </eesti>
<inglise>Upon entry into the police service, police officers shall take the following police oath: </inglise>
<eesti>"Astudes politseiteenistusse, annan mina, (ees- ja perekonnanimi), vande olla ustav Eesti p&otilde;hiseaduslikule korrale, juhinduda k&otilde;rvalekaldumatult seadustest, hoida riigi- ja ametisaladust, rakendada minule antud v&otilde;imu &otilde;iglaselt ja erapooletult ning t&auml;ita ausalt ja kohusetundlikult teenistuskohustusi." </eesti>
<inglise>"Upon entry into the police service, I, (given name and surname), shall take an oath to be loyal to the constitutional order of Estonia, comply unwaveringly with legislation, maintain state and professional secrets, use the authority given to me in a just and impartial manner, and perform the duties in an honest and conscientious manner." </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseivande andmine </eesti>
<inglise>Taking police oath </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Iga teenistusse astuv politseiametnik annab politseivande. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Every police officer shall take the police oath upon entry into the service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseivande andmine toimub pidulikult, riigilipu juures. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The taking of the police oath takes place in a festive manner and under the national flag. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseivannet andev politseiametnik loeb ette politseivande ja kirjutab alla politseivande tekstile. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon taking the police oath, police officers shall read out the police oath and sign the text of the police oath. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Politseivande v&otilde;tab vastu siseminister v&otilde;i Kaitsepolitseiameti v&otilde;i Politseiameti v&otilde;i muu politseiasutuse v&otilde;i politsei&otilde;ppeasutuse juht. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The police oath shall be administered by the Minister of Internal Affairs, head of the Security Police Board or the Police Board or the head of any other police authority or police training institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Politseikadett annab politseivande &otilde;ppeasutuse pidulikul l&otilde;petamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Police cadets shall take the police oath in the official graduation ceremony of a training institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Politseiametniku v&otilde;i politseikadeti poolt allakirjutatud politseivande teksti hoitakse koos teenistuslehega. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The text of the police oath signed by a police officer or cadet shall be kept together with the service record. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametnike ametisse nimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment of police officers to office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiameti juhi nimetab ametisse viieks aastaks Vabariigi Valitsus siseministri ettepanekul, kuulates &auml;ra Riigikogu &otilde;iguskomisjoni seisukoha. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Government of the Republic shall, on the proposal of the Minister of Internal Affairs, appoint to office the head of the Police Board for a term of five years after having considered the opinion of the Legal Committee of the Riigikogu (2). </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiameti juhti ei tohi nimetada ametisse rohkem kui kaheks ametiajaks j&auml;rjestikku. </eesti>
<inglise>The head of the Police Board shall not be appointed to office for more than two consecutive terms. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaitsepolitseiameti peadirektor nimetatakse ametisse julgeolekuasutuste seaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The National Security Police Commissioner shall be appointed to office pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Security Authorities Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiameti ja Kaitsepolitseiameti juhi aset&auml;itjad nimetab ametisse siseminister vastava ameti juhi ettepanekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The deputy head of the Police Board and the deputy head of the Security Police Board shall be appointed to office by the Minister of Internal Affairs on the proposal of the head of the corresponding Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Sisekaitseakadeemia politseiametnikud nimetab ametisse akadeemia rektor. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The police officers of the Estonian Public Service Academy shall be appointed to office by the Rector of the Academy. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teised k&otilde;rgemad politseiametnikud nimetab ametisse vastavalt Politseiameti ja Kaitsepolitseiameti juht. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Other higher police officers shall be appointed to office by the head of the Police Board and the head of the Security Police Board respectively. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Politseiprefektuuri juht ning Kaitsepolitseiameti regionaalse struktuuri&uuml;ksuse juht nimetatakse ametisse viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The heads of police prefectures and heads of regional structural units of the Security Police Board shall be appointed to office for a term of five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1, 2, 3 ja 4 nimetamata politseiametnikud nimetab ametisse vastava asutuse juht. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Police officers not specified in subsections (1), (2), (3) or (4) of this section shall be appointed to office by the head of the corresponding body. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametnike ametisse nimetamise tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for appointment of police officers to office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiameti ja Kaitsepolitseiameti juhiks v&otilde;ib nimetada isiku, kes on vahetult enne ametisse nimetamist t&ouml;&ouml;tanud v&auml;hemalt kolm aastat kas Politseiameti v&otilde;i Kaitsepolitseiameti juhi aset&auml;itjana v&otilde;i Politseiameti v&otilde;i Kaitsepolitseiameti struktuuri&uuml;ksuse, politseiasutuse v&otilde;i politsei&otilde;ppeasutuse juhina. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Any person who has worked as the deputy head of the Police Board or the Security Police Board, as the head of a structural unit of the Police Board or Security Police Board or as the head of a police authority or police training institution for at least three years immediately before appointment to office may be appointed as the head of the Police Board or head of the Security Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiameti ja Kaitsepolitseiameti juhi aset&auml;itjaks, Politseiameti ja Kaitsepolitseiameti struktuuri&uuml;ksuse, politseiasutuse ja politsei&otilde;ppeasutuse juhiks v&otilde;ib nimetada isiku, kes on vahetult enne ametisse nimetamist t&ouml;&ouml;tanud v&auml;hemalt kolm aastat k&otilde;rgema politseiametnikuna. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Any person who has worked as a higher police officer for at least three years immediately before appointment to office may be appointed as the deputy head of the Police Board or Security Police Board, as the head of a structural unit of the Police Board or Security Police Board, or as the head of a police authority or police training institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Muu k&otilde;rgema politseiametniku ametikohale v&otilde;ib nimetada isiku, kes on v&auml;hemalt kaks aastat t&ouml;&ouml;tanud politseiametnike 3. v&otilde;i 4. ametiastmesse kuuluval politseiametniku ametikohal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Any person who has worked in the position of police officer belonging to the third or forth official rank of police officers for at least two years may be appointed to another position of higher police officer. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Erandkorras v&otilde;ib komissariks nimetada teadus- v&otilde;i kutsekraadi omava isiku v&otilde;i isiku, kes enne ametisse nimetamist on v&auml;hemalt kaks aastat t&ouml;&ouml;tanud kohtunikuna, vandeadvokaadina, prokur&ouml;rina (v&auml;lja arvatud abiprokur&ouml;rina), k&otilde;rgema vanglaametnikuna v&otilde;i notarina. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) As an exception, a person who has a research or professional degree or has worked as a judge, sworn advocate, prosecutor (with the exception of assistant prosecutor), higher prison officer or a notary for at least two years before appointment to office may be appointed as a superintendent. </inglise>
<eesti>(19.01.2000 j&otilde;ust.16.02.2000 - RT I 2000, 10, 57) </eesti>
<inglise>(19.01.2000 entered into force 16.02.2000 - RT I 2000, 10, 57) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Politseiametnike 3. v&otilde;i 4. ametiastmesse kuuluvale politseiametniku ametikohale v&otilde;ib nimetada isiku, kes on v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he aasta t&ouml;&ouml;tanud politseiametnike 2. ametiastmesse kuuluval politseiametniku ametikohal. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Any person who has worked in the position of police officer belonging to the second official rank of police officers for at least one year may be appointed to the position of police officer belonging to the third or fourth official rank of police officers. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Politseiametnike 2. ametiastmesse kuuluvale politseiametniku ametikohale v&otilde;ib nimetada isiku, kes on v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he aasta t&ouml;&ouml;tanud noorempolitseiametniku ametikohal. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Any person who has worked in the position of junior police officer for at least one year may be appointed to the position of police officer belonging to the second official rank of police officers. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Erandkorras v&otilde;ib vanempolitseiametniku ametikohale nimetada k&otilde;rgharidusega isiku, kelle haridus vastab sellele ametikohale etten&auml;htud haridusn&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) As an exception, a person who has higher education and whose education meets the educational requirements for the position may be appointed to the position of senior police officer. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Politseiametniku v&otilde;ib ametisse nimetada konkursita. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Police officers may be appointed to office without a competition. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Internetis teabe avaldamine politseiametnike vabade ametikohtade kohta </eesti>
<inglise>Publication of information on Internet on vacant positions of police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teave politseiasutuste ja politsei&otilde;ppeasutuste vabanevate v&otilde;i vabade ametikohtade ja ametikohale nimetamise tingimuste, sealhulgas konkursi tingimuste kohta peab olema avaldatud Politseiameti Interneti kodulehek&uuml;ljel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Information on positions about to become or presently vacant in police authorities and police training institutions, and on the requirements of appointment to office, including the competition conditions, shall be made public on the web site of the Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teavet ei avaldata nende politseiametnike ametikohtade kohta, kelle &uuml;lesandeks on vaid j&auml;litustegevus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) No information shall be made public on the positions of police officer which solely concern surveillance. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud teabe avaldamise korra kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for publication of information specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku &uuml;leviimine </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of Police Officers </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku tema n&otilde;usolekuta &uuml;leviimine </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of police officers without their consent </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&auml;iendavalt avaliku teenistuse seaduses s&auml;testatud juhtudele v&otilde;ib politseiametniku teenistuse huvides tema n&otilde;usolekuta &uuml;le viia muule politseiametniku ametikohale: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In addition to the cases specified in the Public Service Act, a police officer may, in the interest of the service, be transferred to another position of police officer without the consent of the police officer: </inglise>
<eesti>1) sama ametiastme piires samas v&otilde;i teises politseiasutuses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) within the same official rank in the same or another police authority; </inglise>
<eesti>2) politseiametnike p&otilde;higrupi ametiastmete piires, sealhulgas madalamale ametikohale, kui &uuml;leviimine on seotud politseiasutuse v&otilde;i politsei&otilde;ppeasutuse &uuml;mberkorraldamise v&otilde;i tegevuse l&otilde;petamise v&otilde;i teenistujate koosseisude koondamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>2) within the official ranks of the basic categories of police officers, including transfer to a position of a lower rank, if such transfer is due to the reorganisation or dissolution of or lay-offs in a police authority or police training institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;leviimine, millega kaasneb politseiametniku elukoha muutus, on keelatud, kui tema viimasest n&otilde;usolekuta &uuml;leviimisest, millega kaasnes elukoha muutus, on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud v&auml;hem kui viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Any transfer which results in the change of a police officer's residence shall be prohibited if the last transfer which resulted in the change of residence took place without the consent of the police officer less than five years ago. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku tema n&otilde;usolekuta &uuml;leviimise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Authority to transfer police officers without their consent </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametniku tema n&otilde;usolekuta &uuml;leviimise &otilde;igus on isikul, kellel on politseiametniku sellele ametikohale nimetamise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The right to transfer a police officer without his or her consent lies with the person who has the authority to appoint the police officer to office. </inglise>
<eesti>Noorem- ja vanempolitseiametniku &uuml;hest politseiasutusest (v&auml;lja arvatud Kaitsepolitseiamet) teise &uuml;leviimise &otilde;igus on Politseiameti juhil. </eesti>
<inglise>The right to transfer junior or senior police officers from one police authority to another (with the exception of the Security Police Board) lies with the head of the Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametniku tema n&otilde;usolekuta teisele ametikohale Kaitsepolitseiametisse &uuml;leviimise &otilde;igus ning Kaitsepolitseiameti politseiametniku ametikohale teises politseiasutuses &uuml;leviimise &otilde;igus on siseministril. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The right to transfer a police officer without his or her consent to another position in the Security Police Board or to the position of police officer of the Security Police Board in another police authority lies with the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagatised n&otilde;usolekuta &uuml;leviimise korral </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantees upon transfer without consent </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametniku teisele ametikohale tema n&otilde;usolekuta &uuml;leviimisest teenistuse huvides on &uuml;leviimise &otilde;igust omav isik kohustatud politseiametnikule kirjalikult ette teatama v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kuu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who has the authority to transfer a police officer in the interest of the service without the consent of the police officer to another position shall notify the police officer thereof in writing at least one month in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku elukoha muutusega seotud &uuml;leviimisest peab ette teatama v&auml;hemalt kaks kuud. </eesti>
<inglise>A notice concerning a transfer of a police officer which results in the change of his or her residence shall be given at least two months in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;leviidud politseiametnikule: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A police officer who is transferred shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) s&auml;ilitatakse senine palk, kui palk uuel ametikohal on v&auml;iksem senisest palgast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) continue to receive his or her former salary if the salary at the new position is smaller than the former salary; </inglise>
<eesti>2) makstakse &uuml;hekordse h&uuml;vitisena nelja kuu ametipalk, kui &uuml;leviimine on seotud ametniku elukoha muutusega. </eesti>
<inglise>2) receive his or her four months' salary as a single benefit if the transfer results in the change of residence of the officer. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiametniku &uuml;leviimine, millega kaasneb elukoha muutus, on lubatud &uuml;ksnes juhul, kui ta kindlustatakse uues paikkonnas t&ouml;&ouml;andja eluruumiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The transfer of a police officer which results in the change of his or her residence is permitted only if the police officer is provided with housing in the new locality by the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja eluruumi andmise tingimused ning eluruumi suuruse ja heakorrastatuse n&otilde;uded kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for provision of housing by employer and the requirements for the size and condition of the housing shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;andja eluruumi vabastamisel h&uuml;vitatakse politseiametnikule tema poolt eluruumi remontimiseks ja heakorrastamiseks tehtud kulutused juhul, kui kulutuste vajalikkuses ja suuruses oli eelnevalt kokku lepitud vastavalt Politseiameti v&otilde;i Kaitsepolitseiametiga ning selle kohta on s&otilde;lmitud kirjalik leping. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon vacating the housing provided by an employer as specified in subsection (3) of this section, the police officer shall be compensated for the expenses incurred by him or her for the repair and reconditioning of the housing provided that the necessity and amount of the expenses was agreed upon in advance with the Police Board or the Security Police Board, as appropriate, and a written agreement was concluded with reference thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingu t&uuml;&uuml;ptingimused kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The standard conditions of such contract shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppej&otilde;uks &uuml;leviidud politseiametniku tagatised </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantees of police officers transferred to position of lecturer </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnikule, kes on tema n&otilde;usolekul v&otilde;i omal algatusel &uuml;le viidud v&otilde;i nimetatud Sisekaitseakadeemia v&otilde;i politsei&otilde;ppeasutusse politseiametnikust &otilde;ppej&otilde;u ametikohale &uuml;heks kuni viieks &otilde;ppeaastaks, laienevad &sect; 17 l&otilde;igetes 2, 3 ja 4 etten&auml;htud tagatised kogu tema t&ouml;&ouml;tamise ajaks nimetatud &otilde;ppeasutuse politseiametnikust &otilde;ppej&otilde;u ametikohal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The guarantees provided for in subsections 17 (2), (3) and (4) of this Act extend to a police officer who is transferred with his or her consent or on his or her initiative, or appointed to the position of lecturer as a police officer at the Estonian Public Service Academy or a police training institution for one up to five academic years, for the whole period of employment in the position of lecturer as a police officer of such training institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17; 11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17; 11.10.2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel viiakse &otilde;ppej&otilde;una t&ouml;&ouml;tanud politseiametnik tema soovil tagasi samale v&otilde;i teisele ametikohale sama ametiastme piires, ametikoha puudumisel aga m&otilde;nele muule ametikohale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) After expiry of the term specified in subsection (1) of this section, a police officer who is employed as a lecturer shall be transferred at his or her request to the same position or to another position within the same official rank; if such position is not available, the police officer shall be transferred to another position. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku ametih&uuml;ved </eesti>
<inglise>Police Officers' Benefits Related to Office </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametnike palgaastmestik </eesti>
<inglise>Salary scale of police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnikele kehtestatakse diferentseeritud palgaastmestik 1. kuni 10. palgaastmeni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A differentiated salary scale of salary grades from 1 to 10 shall be established for police officers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametniku palgaaste vastab tema ametiastmele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The salary grade of a police officer shall correspond to his or her official rank. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiametniku palgaastme siseselt v&otilde;idakse kehtestada diferentseeritud palgam&auml;&auml;rad erineva kategooria, kvalifikatsiooni, piirkonna v&otilde;i asutuse ametnikele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Within a salary grade of police officers, differentiated salary rates may be established for officers of different categories, qualifications, districts or bodies. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Politseiametnike palgaastmestiku 1. palgaastme madalaim palgam&auml;&auml;r (politseiametniku miinimumpalk) on 4200 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The minimum salary rate of the first salary grade of the salary scale of police officers (the minimum salary of police officers) is 4 200 kroons. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Politseiametnike palgaastmetele vastavad, sealhulgas diferentseeritud palgam&auml;&auml;rad ja nende kasutamise erisused kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The salary rates, including differentiated salary rates, corresponding to the salary grades of police officers and the specifications of their use shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(5 (1)) Juhul kui politseiametniku palgaastmestiku j&auml;rgset palgam&auml;&auml;ra v&otilde;idakse diferentseerida (suurendada) kahel v&otilde;i enamal alusel, siis liidetakse diferentseerimise m&auml;&auml;rad (protsendid) &uuml;htseks diferentseerimise m&auml;&auml;raks (protsendiks), mille alusel arvutatakse diferentseeritud palgam&auml;&auml;r. </eesti>
<inglise>(5 (1)) If the salary rate of a police office according to the salary scale can be differentiated (increased) on two or more bases, the rates (percentages) of differentiation shall be added up to a total rate (percentage) of differentiation on the basis of which the differentiated salary rate shall be calculated. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Vabariigi Valitsus v&otilde;ib &uuml;ks kord aastas suurendada k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud politseiametniku miinimumpalga m&auml;&auml;ra. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Government of the Republic may increase the minimum salary rate of police officers established by this Act once a year. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;nede politseiametnike t&ouml;&ouml;tasustamise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications of remuneration of some police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) J&auml;litustegevust teostava politseiametniku, v&auml;lja arvatud Kaitsepolitseiameti politseiametniku ametipalka suurendatakse 10 kuni 50 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The salary of police officers engaged in surveillance, except police officers of the Security Police Board, shall be increased by 10 - 50 per cent. </inglise>
<eesti>Nende ametikohtade loetelu v&otilde;i loetelusse arvamise tingimused kehtestab siseminister k&auml;skkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>A list of such positions or requirements for inclusion of positions in the list shall be established by a directive of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud loetelusse kantud politseiametnikele ei maksta lisatasu &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;tamise eest &otilde;htusel ja &ouml;isel ajal ning puhkep&auml;eval ja riiklikul p&uuml;hal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Police officers included in the list specified in subsection (1) of this section shall not receive additional remuneration for working overtime or in the evening or night time, nor for working on days off or public holidays. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiametniku palgaastme palgam&auml;&auml;ra muutmisel s&auml;ilitatakse politseiametnikule sellel ametikohal t&ouml;&ouml;tamise ajaks tema senine palgaastme palgam&auml;&auml;r, kuid mitte kauemaks kui kaheks aastaks, kui palgaastme uus palgam&auml;&auml;r on v&auml;iksem tema senisest palgam&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If, upon a change in the salary rate of a police officer, the new salary rate of the salary grade is lower than his or her former salary rate, the police officer shall continue to receive the former salary rate of the salary grade until he or she is employed in that position, but for not longer than two years. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Politseikadeti &otilde;ppepraktikat juhendavale politseiametnikule v&otilde;ib maksta lisatasu kuni 5 protsenti juhendava politseiametniku palgaastme palgam&auml;&auml;rast iga juhendatava kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Additional remuneration may be paid to a police officer instructing police cadets in their practical training in the amount equal to 5 per cent of the salary rate of the salary grade of the police officer payable for each instructed cadet. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Toetus politseiametniku hukkumise, p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks tunnistamise, haigestumise ja talle kehavigastuse tekitamise korral </eesti>
<inglise>Allowances upon death, declaration of permanent incapacity for work, illness of or causing of bodily injuries to police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmisel v&otilde;i seoses teenistusega politseis hukkunud politseiametniku perekonnaliikmetele ja tema &uuml;lalpidamisel olnud isikutele maksab riik &uuml;hekordset toetust hukkunu k&uuml;mne aasta palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a police officer dies in the performance of his or her duties or in connection with the service in the police, the state shall pay the family members and persons who were maintained by the deceased police officer a single allowance in an amount equal to ten years' wages of the deceased. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmisel v&otilde;i seoses teenistusega politseis hukkunud politseiametniku matuse kulud kannab riik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The cost of the funeral of a police officer who dies in the performance of his or her duties or in connection with the service in the police shall be borne by the state. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmisel v&otilde;i seoses teenistusega politseis p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud politseiametnikule makstakse &uuml;hekordset toetust: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A police officer who is declared permanently incapacitated for work due to the performance of his or her duties or in connection with the service in the police shall be paid a single allowance upon: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime osalise kaotuse korral, mis ei toonud kaasa politseiteenistusest vabastamist, - tema &uuml;he aasta palga ulatuses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) partial loss of capacity for work which did not result in release from the police service, to the extent of his or her one year's salary; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime osalise kaotuse korral, mis t&otilde;i kaasa politseiteenistusest vabastamise, - tema kahe aasta palga ulatuses; </eesti>
<inglise>2) partial loss of capacity for work which resulted in release from the police service, to the extent of his or her two years' salary; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime t&auml;ieliku kaotuse korral - tema seitsme aasta palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>3) total loss of capacity for work, to the extent of his or her seven years' salary. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Politseiametnikule, kellele teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmisel v&otilde;i seoses teenistusega politseis tekitati terviserikkega kehavigastus, millega ei kaasnenud p&uuml;sivat t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetust, makstakse &uuml;hekordset toetust &uuml;he kuu palga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A police officer who, in the performance of his or her duties or in connection with the service in the police, receives a bodily injury which damages his or her health but does not result in permanent incapacity for work, shall be paid a single allowance in an amount equal to his or her one month's salary. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmisel v&otilde;i seoses teenistusega politseis vigastada saanud v&otilde;i haigestunud politseiametniku ravi- ja ravimikulud kannab riik. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Medical expenses and the cost of medicinal products of police officers who receive injuries or fall ill in the performance of their duties or in connection with the service in the police shall be borne by the state. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud toetuste ja kulude arvutamise ja maksmise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The procedure for calculation and payment of the allowances and costs provided for in this section shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku pension </eesti>
<inglise>Pensions for police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnikul, kellel on v&auml;hemalt 20-aastane politseiteenistuse staa&zcaron;, tekib 50-aastaselt &otilde;igus politseiametniku pensionile 50 protsendi ulatuses tema viimasest politseiametniku ametipalgast v&otilde;i teenistuse viie viimase aasta hulgast valitud soodsaimast politseiametniku ametipalgast ametikoha j&auml;rgi, millel ta teenis v&auml;hemalt 12 kuud j&auml;rjest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A police officer whose length of police service is at least 20 years has the right to receive a pension for police officers when he or she attains 50 years of age in the amount of 50% of the of the police officer's last salary or of the most favourable salary corresponding to his or her position earned by police officer during the last five years of the police officer's service, provided that he or her she served in the position for at least twelve consecutive months. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametnikul, kes on teenistusest vabastatud vanuse, tervisliku seisundi v&otilde;i koosseisude koondamise t&otilde;ttu ning on teenistusest vabastamise p&auml;evaks saanud 55-aastaseks ja kelle &uuml;ldine pensioni&otilde;iguslik v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron; on v&auml;hemalt 25 aastat, millest 12 aastat ja 6 kuud on teenitud politseiametnikuna, on &otilde;igus saada politseiametniku pensioni 30 protsendi ulatuses tema viimasest politseiametniku ametipalgast v&otilde;i teenistuse viie viimase aasta hulgast valitud soodsaimast politseiametniku ametipalgast ametikoha j&auml;rgi, millel ta teenis v&auml;hemalt 12 kuud j&auml;rjest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A police officer who is released from service due to age, state of health or lay-offs in the staff and who by the date of his or her release from service has attained 55 years of age and who has completed at least twenty five years of pensionable service or whose accumulation period is at least twenty five years, twelve years and six months of which the person served on the position of a police officer, has the right to receive a pension for police officers in the amount of 30% of the police officer's last salary or of the most favourable salary corresponding to his or her position earned by police officer during the last five years of the police officer's service, provided that he or her she served in the position for at least twelve consecutive months </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Iga aasta eest, mille v&otilde;rra politseiametniku politseiteenistuse staa&zcaron; &uuml;letab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud politseiteenistuse staa&zcaron;i, suurendatakse politseiametniku pensioni 2,5 protsendi v&otilde;rra tema pensioni arvestamise aluseks olnud ametipalgast, kuid maksimaalselt kuni 75 protsendini vastavast ametipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The amount of pension for police officers shall be increased for each year by which the length of the police service of the police officer exceeds the length of service provided in subsection (1) or (2) of this section in the amount equivalent to 2.5 per cent of the salary based on which the pension of a police officer was calculated, however in a maximum amount of 75 per cent of the corresponding salary. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Politseiameti v&otilde;i Kaitsepolitseiameti juhi politseiametniku pensioni suurus, s&otilde;ltumata tema &uuml;ldisest politseiteenistuse staa&zcaron;ist ja vanusest, on alates tema teise t&auml;ieliku ametiaja l&otilde;ppemise p&auml;evast 75 protsenti tema viimasest ametipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The amount of pension for police officers of a head of the Police Board or head of the Security Police Board shall be 75 per cent of his or her last salary as of the date of expiry of his or her second term of office, regardless of the overall length of his or her police service and age. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui muutub politseiametniku pensioni arvestamise aluseks oleva ametikoha ametipalk, arvutatakse pension &uuml;mber. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The pension shall be recalculated if the salary, corresponding to the position based on which a pension for police officers was calculated, changes. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul makstakse pensioni muutunud suuruses, alates ametipalga muutumisele j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesest kuup&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the pension shall be paid in the altered amount as of the first day of the month following the month on which the salary was changed. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Politseiametniku pensioni ei suurendata avaliku teenistuse seaduse (RT I 1995, 16, 228; 1999, 7, 112; 10, 155; 16, 271 ja 276; 2000, 25, 144 ja 145; 28, 167; 102, 672; 2001, 7, 17 ja 18; 17, 78; 42, 233; 47, 260) &sect; 57 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The pension of police officer shall not be increased pursuant to the provisions of &sect; 57 of the Public Service Act (RT I 1995, 16, 228; 1999, 7, 112; 10, 155; 16, 271 and 276; 2000, 25, 144 and 145; 28, 167; 102, 672; 2001, 7, 17 and 18; 17, 78; 42, 233; 47, 260). </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Politseiametniku pensioni ei maksta politseiametniku ametikohal t&ouml;&ouml;tamise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A pension for police officers shall not be paid if a person is working in the position of a police officer. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikule, kes j&auml;tkab t&ouml;&ouml;tamist m&otilde;nel muul kutsealal v&otilde;i ametikohal, makstakse politseiametniku pensioni t&auml;ies ulatuses, s&otilde;ltumata sissetuleku suurusest. </eesti>
<inglise>A pension for police officers shall be paid out to the full extent to a person who continues working in any other profession or position regardless of the amount of income earned by such person. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Politseiametniku pension m&auml;&auml;ratakse eluajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) A pension for police officer is granted for life. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Politseiametnikule, kellel on samaaegselt &otilde;igus mitmele k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i teistes seadustes s&auml;testatud riiklikule pensionile, m&auml;&auml;ratakse &uuml;ks riikliku pensioni liik tema valikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Police officers who have the right to receive several of the state pensions provided for in this Act or other Acts concurrently shall be granted one class of state pension of their choice. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud politseiametniku pensionile ei teki &otilde;igust politseiametnikul, kes on teenistusest vabastatud s&uuml;&uuml;dim&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumisel, millega talle m&otilde;isteti karistus tahtlikult toimepandud kuriteo eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) The right to receive a pension for police officers pursuant to this section does not apply to a police officer who has been released from service upon the entry into force of a judgment of conviction by a court by which by which a punishment is imposed on the person for and intentionally committed criminal offence. </inglise>
<eesti>(11) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud politseiametniku pensionile ei teki &otilde;igust politseiametnikul, kes on politseiteenistusest vabastatud teenistuskohustuste s&uuml;&uuml;lise t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise v&otilde;i mitten&otilde;uetekohase t&auml;itmise eest v&otilde;i joobnuna teenistuses viibimise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(11) The right to receive a pension for police officers pursuant to this section does not apply to a police officer who has been released from service due to the wrongful non-performance or unsatisfactory performance of duties, including intoxication while in the service. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21 (2). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21 (2). </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiteenistuse staa&zcaron; </eesti>
<inglise>Length of police service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiteenistuse staa&zcaron;i hulka, mis annab &otilde;iguse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 21 (1) s&auml;testatud politseiametniku pensionile, arvatakse teenistuse aeg politseiametniku ametikohal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A period of service in the position of police officer shall be included in the length of police service which gives the right to receive a pension for police officers provided for in &sect; 21 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiteenistuse staa&zcaron;i hulka, mis annab &otilde;iguse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 21 (1) s&auml;testatud politseiametniku pensionile, arvatakse samuti k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi punktides 1-4 nimetatud teenistuse v&otilde;i &otilde;ppimise aeg, kui sellele j&auml;rgnes teenistus politseiametniku ametikohal: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A period of service or study specified in clauses 1) -4) of this section provided it was followed by service in the position of police officer shall also be included in the length of police service which gives the right to receive a pension for police officers provided for in &sect; 21 (1) of this Act: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &otilde;ppimise aeg politsei&otilde;ppeasutuses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) period of study in a police training institution; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teenistuse aeg Eesti Vabariigi Riikliku Kohtueelse Uurimise Ameti uurijana ja uurimisala juhtivt&ouml;&ouml;tajana (peadirektor, peadirektori aset&auml;itja, uurimisn&otilde;unik, uurimisb&uuml;roo direktor, abidirektor, uurimisosakonna juhataja, uurimisala peaspetsialist, uurija); </eesti>
<inglise>2) period of service as a preliminary investigator or senior preliminary investigation official of the Pre-trial Investigation Authority of the Republic of Estonia (director general, deputy to director general, adviser in preliminary investigation, director of bureau of preliminary investigation, deputy director, head of department of preliminary investigation, chief specialist in preliminary investigation, preliminary investigator); </inglise>
<eesti>3) tegevteenistuse aeg Eesti kaitsev&auml;es; </eesti>
<inglise>3) period of active service in the Estonian Defence Forces; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teenistusaeg teiste riikide siseasjade organite rea- ja juhtivkoosseisu ametikohtadel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) period of service as members of rank or commanding staff of authorities of internal affairs of other states. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teenistuse aeg enne 1992. aasta 1. juulit kohtunikuna, prokur&ouml;rij&auml;relvalve t&ouml;&ouml;tajana v&otilde;i eeluurimisorgani uurimisala t&ouml;&ouml;tajana arvatakse politseiteenistuse staa&zcaron;i hulka, mis annab &otilde;iguse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 21 (1) s&auml;testatud politseiametniku pensionile, kui sellelt ametikohalt asuti teenistusse politseiametniku ametikohale v&otilde;i kui sellele j&auml;rgnes k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 1-3 s&auml;testatud teenistuse v&otilde;i &otilde;ppimise aeg ja teenistus politseiametniku ametikohal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Period of service before 1 July 1992 as a judge, employee of a prosecutor's office with supervisory control duties or employee of a preliminary investigation authority with preliminary investigation duties, provided it was followed by service in the position of police officer or period of service or study provided for in clauses (2) 1) -3) of this section and service in the position of police officer, shall be included in the length of police service which gives the right to receive a pension for police officers provided for in &sect; 21 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Politseiteenistuse staa&zcaron;i hulka arvestatakse teenistuse aeg politseiametnikuna alates 1991. aasta 1. m&auml;rtsist kuni 1994. aasta 1. septembrini sooduskorras kolmekordselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The period of service as a police officer from 1 March 1991 to 1 September 1994 shall be included in the length of police service under favourable conditions multiplied by three. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21 (3). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21 (3). </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension </eesti>
<inglise>Pension for incapacity for work for police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnikul, kes on t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt kaotanud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime haiguse v&otilde;i vigastuse t&otilde;ttu, mis tekkis seoses teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisega v&otilde;i politseiametniku poolt kuriteo t&otilde;kestamisel, tekib &otilde;igus politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensionile p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse tekkimise p&auml;evast alates. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A police officer who is totally or partially incapacitated for work due to illness or injury as a result of the performance of his or her duties or the combating of a criminal offence has the right to receive a pension for incapacity for work as of the date on which his or her permanent incapacity for work arose. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotuse protsent, selle tekkimise aeg ja p&otilde;hjused tuvastatakse riikliku pensionikindlustuse seaduses (RT I 1998, 64/65, 1009; 2001, 9, 42) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The percentage and time of and reasons for loss of capacity for work of a police officer shall be established pursuant to the procedure provided for in the State Pension Insurance Act (RT I 1998, 64/65, 1009; 2001, 9, 42). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension on t&auml;ieliku p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse korral 100 protsenti politseiametniku viimasest ametipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the case of total and permanent incapacity for work, the amount of pension for incapacity for work for police officers shall be equal to 100 per cent of the police officer's last salary. </inglise>
<eesti>Osalise p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse korral moodustab politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotuse protsendile vastava protsendi politseiametniku viimasest ametipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of partial and permanent loss of capacity for work, the amount of pension for incapacity for work for police officers shall be equal to the percentage of the police officer's last salary which corresponds to the percentage of the loss of his or her capacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametnikule, kelle t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotuse protsent on v&auml;iksem kui 40 protsenti, politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni ei m&auml;&auml;rata. </eesti>
<inglise>A pension for incapacity for work for police officers shall not be granted to a police officer if the percentage of the loss of his or her capacity for work is less than 40. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui muutub p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotuse protsent v&otilde;i politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni arvutamise aluseks oleva ametikoha ametipalk, arvutatakse politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension &uuml;mber. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The pension for incapacity for work for police officers shall be recalculated if the percentage of the loss of the capacity for work or the salary of the position based on which the pension for police officers was calculated changes. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul makstakse pensioni muutunud suuruses alates j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesest kuup&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the pension shall be paid in the altered amount as of the first day of the following month. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui politseiametnikul on tema t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks tunnistamise p&auml;evaks politseiametniku pensioni m&auml;&auml;ramiseks n&otilde;utav staa&zcaron;, m&auml;&auml;ratakse tema soovil talle politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension politseiametniku pensioni suuruses. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If, by the date a police officer is declared incapacitated for work, the length of his or her service meets the requirement for the grant of a pension for police officers, a pension for incapacity for work for police officers shall, at his or her request, be granted to him or her in the amount of the pension for police officers. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni saav politseiametnik tunnistati t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks enne riikliku pensionikindlustuse seaduse &sect;-s 7 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioniikka j&otilde;udmist, j&auml;tkatakse talle sellesse ikka j&otilde;udmisel senise pensioni maksmist eluaegselt, kohaldades k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatud pensioni &uuml;mberarvutamise korda. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If a police officer receiving a pension for incapacity for work for police officers was declared incapacitated for work before he or she attained a pensionable age provided for in &sect; 7 of the State Pension Insurance Act, then after attaining the pensionable age, the person shall continue to receive such pension during his or her lifetime; however, the procedure for recalculating pensions provided for in subsection (4) of this section shall be applied thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni saavale isikule makstakse pension v&auml;lja t&auml;ies ulatuses, s&otilde;ltumata tema sissetuleku suurusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Persons to whom a pension for police officers or pension for incapacity for work for police officers is granted shall be paid the full amount of the pension regardless of the amount of income he or she receives. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Politseiametnikule, kellel on samaaegselt &otilde;igus mitmele k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i teistes seadustes s&auml;testatud riiklikule pensionile, m&auml;&auml;ratakse &uuml;ks riikliku pensioni liik tema valikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Police officers who have the right to receive several of the state pensions provided for in this Act or other Acts concurrently shall be granted one class of state pension of their choice. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21 (4). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21 (4). </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku pensioni ja politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni taotlemine, m&auml;&auml;ramine ja maksmine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for, grant and payment of pension for police officers and pension for incapacity for work for police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametniku pensioni ja politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni taotlemisel rakendatakse riikliku pensionikindlustuse seaduse &sect; 36 s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The provisions of &sect; 36 of the State Pension Insurance Act apply upon application for a pension for police officers and pension for incapacity for work for police officers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametniku pension ja politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension m&auml;&auml;ratakse vastavale pensionile &otilde;iguse tekkimise p&auml;evast, kui pensionitaotlus esitati kolme kuu jooksul, arvates pensionile &otilde;iguse tekkimisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A pension for police officers and pension for incapacity for work for police officers shall be granted as of the date on which the right to receive the pension arises provided that the application is submitted within three months after the date on which the right to receive the pension arises. </inglise>
<eesti>Teistel juhtudel m&auml;&auml;ratakse politseiametniku pension ja politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension alates pensioni taotlemise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>In other cases, pensions for police officers and pensions for incapacity for work for police officers shall be granted as of the date of application for the pensions. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensioni m&auml;&auml;ramisel rakendatakse riikliku pensionikindlustuse seaduse &sect; 37 s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>The provisions of &sect; 37 of the State Pension Insurance Act apply upon grant of the pensions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiametniku pensioni ja politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni maksmisel rakendatakse riikliku pensionikindlustuse seaduse s&auml;tteid, kui k&auml;esolev seadus ei s&auml;testa teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The provisions of the State Pension Insurance Act apply upon payment of pensions for police officers and pensions for incapacity for work for police officers, unless otherwise provided by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud politseiametniku pensioni ja politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni makstakse riigieelarve vahenditest Siseministeeriumi eelarve kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Pensions for police officers and pensions for incapacity for work for police officers provided by this Act shall be paid out of state budget funds through the budget of the Ministry of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud politseiametniku pensioni v&otilde;i politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni arvutamiseks, m&auml;&auml;ramiseks, &uuml;mberarvutamiseks ja maksmiseks on Vabariigi Valitsusel v&otilde;i tema m&auml;&auml;ratud p&auml;deval ministril &otilde;igus anda m&auml;&auml;rusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Government of the Republic or a competent minister appointed by the Government of the Republic has the right to issue regulations for the calculation, grant, recalculation and payment of the pensions for police officers and pensions for incapacity for work for police officers provided by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Varalise kahju h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for proprietary damage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametniku teenistus&uuml;lesande t&auml;itmise k&auml;igus politseiametnikule v&otilde;i tema perekonnaliikmele tekitatud otsese varalise kahju h&uuml;vitab riik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The state shall compensate a police officer or his or her family members for direct proprietary damage which the police officer suffers in the performance of his or her duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Varalise kahju h&uuml;vitamise tingimused, piirm&auml;&auml;ra ja korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The conditions for, limits of and procedure for compensation for proprietary damage shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku terviseuuringud </eesti>
<inglise>Medical examinations of police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riik tagab politseiametnikule tasuta terviseuuringud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The state shall provide police officers with free medical examinations. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Terviseuuringute l&auml;biviimise tingimused, perioodilisuse ja korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The conditions, regularity and procedure for performance of medical examinations shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hiss&otilde;iduki kasutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Use of public transport </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku poolt &uuml;hiss&otilde;iduki ametis&otilde;itudeks kasutamise tingimused ja kulude h&uuml;vitamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitus m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The conditions for use of public transport for business travel by police officers and the procedure for reimbursement of expenses shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;andja eluruum </eesti>
<inglise>Housing provided by employer </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnikule kindlustatakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja eluruum vajaduse ja v&otilde;imaluse korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Police officers shall be provided with housing by the employer, where necessary and possible. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohalik omavalitsus v&otilde;ib anda valda v&otilde;i linna teenindavale politseiametnikule eluruumi tingimustel ja korras, mis on ette n&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;andja eluruumi andmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A local government may provide police officers who serve in the corresponding rural municipality or city with housing pursuant to the conditions and procedure established for provision of housing by an employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseivormiriietus </eesti>
<inglise>Police uniform </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnikule ja politseikadetile antakse politseivormiriietus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Police officers and cadets shall be provided with police uniforms. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vormiriietuse kirjelduse ja vormiriietuse esemete kandmise t&auml;htajad kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The description of and the term for wearing police clothing items shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vormiriietuse andmise ja kandmise korra kehtestab vastavalt Politseiameti ja Kaitsepolitseiameti juht. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for provision and wearing of uniforms shall be established by the head of the Police Board or the head of the Security Police Board, as appropriate. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Politseiametnikule, kellele ei anta vormiriietust, makstakse h&uuml;vitist vormiriietuse maksumuse ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Police officers who are not provided with uniforms shall receive compensation in an amount equal to the cost of the uniform. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaeg ning puhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Working and Rest Time and Holiday of Police Officers </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; </eesti>
<inglise>Overtime of police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnik on kohustatud t&auml;itma asutuse juhi korraldust teha &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;d j&auml;rgmistel juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Police officers are required to comply with the orders of the head of a police authority to work overtime in the following cases: </inglise>
<eesti>1) riigi julgeoleku tagamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in order to guarantee national security; </inglise>
<eesti>2) riigikaitse vajadusel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for the purposes of national defence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) inimese p&auml;&auml;stmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) for the rescue of people; </inglise>
<eesti>4) abi osutamiseks tulet&otilde;rje- ja p&auml;&auml;stet&ouml;&ouml;del; </eesti>
<inglise>4) for the provision of assistance in fire and rescue work; </inglise>
<eesti>5) loodus&otilde;nnetuse, tulekahju, avarii v&otilde;i katastroofi ennetamiseks v&otilde;i selle tagaj&auml;rgede k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>5) for the prevention of a natural disaster, fire, accident or catastrophe, or for the elimination of consequences thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>6) massilise korratuse &auml;rahoidmiseks ja l&otilde;petamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>6) for the prevention and termination of mass disorders; </inglise>
<eesti>7) korra tagamiseks suur&uuml;ritusel; </eesti>
<inglise>7) for the maintenance of order in public events; </inglise>
<eesti>8) politsei&uuml;lesande t&auml;itmiseks, mida selle ise&auml;rasuste t&otilde;ttu ei ole v&otilde;imalik katkestada v&otilde;i l&otilde;petada; </eesti>
<inglise>8) for the performance of a police task which cannot be suspended or completed due to its particular nature; </inglise>
<eesti>9) muudel seaduses s&auml;testatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>9) in other cases provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametnikku ei ole lubatud rakendada &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;le 8 tunni p&auml;evas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Police officers shall not be required to work overtime for more than 8 hours per day. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahetuse kestus koos &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;ga ei tohi &uuml;letada 16 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>The duration of a shift including overtime shall not exceed 16 hours. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; piirnorm &uuml;he politseiametniku kohta on 300 tundi kalendriaastas. </eesti>
<inglise>The standard limit on overtime per police officer is 300 hours per calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendamine puhkep&auml;eval ja riigip&uuml;hal </eesti>
<inglise>Requiring police officers to work on days off or public holidays </inglise>
<eesti>Asutuse juht v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 27 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud juhtudel politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada puhkep&auml;eval ja riigip&uuml;hal. </eesti>
<inglise>The head of a police authority may require police officers to work on days off or public holidays in the cases specified in subsection 27 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Valveaeg </eesti>
<inglise>On call time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Valveaeg on aeg, millal politseiametnik peab olema asutuse juhtkonnale ja korrapidamisteenistusele kokkulepitud kohas k&auml;ttesaadav edasil&uuml;kkamatute politseitoimingute tegemiseks oma puhkeajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On call time is the time when police officers shall be at the disposal of the management of a body or duty officer's service in agreed locations for the performance of urgent police activities during their rest time. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valveaja kestus ei tohi &uuml;letada 150 tundi kuus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The duration of on call time shall not exceed 150 hours per month. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valveaja eest makstakse lisatasu, mis on 10% politseiametniku tunnipalga m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Additional remuneration equal to ten per cent of the hourly wage rate of a police officer shall be paid for on call time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku puhkuse katkestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Interruption of holiday of police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametniku puhkus v&otilde;idakse katkestada ja ta teenistusse tagasi kutsuda tema n&otilde;usolekul, kuid mitte rohkem kui kahel korral puhkuse v&auml;ltel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A holiday of a police officer may be interrupted and the police officer may be asked to return to the service with his or her consent but not more than twice during one holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Puhkuse katkestamise n&otilde;usolek ei ole vajalik, kui politseiametniku puhkus katkestatakse ja ta kutsutakse teenistusse tagasi k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 27 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1, 2, 3 ja 5 nimetatud juhtumil. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) No consent is required for the interruption of holiday if a police officer's holiday is interrupted and he or she is asked to return to the service in the cases specified in clauses 27 (1) 1), 2), 3) or 5) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku lisapuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Additional holiday of police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnikule antavat lisapuhkust avaliku teenistuse staa&zcaron;i eest ei pea liitma p&otilde;hipuhkusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An additional holiday granted to police officers for the length of public service need not be added to the base holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Asutuse juht v&otilde;ib anda politseiametnikule t&auml;iendavat tasulist lisapuhkust eeskujuliku teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise eest kuni 10 kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The head of a body may grant an additional paid holiday of up to ten calendar days to police officers for excellent performance of duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku muud teenistustingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Other Conditions of Service of Police Officers </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendamine v&auml;ljaspool tema teenistuspiirkonda ja -&uuml;lesandeid </eesti>
<inglise>Requiring police officers to work outside of their service area and beyond their duties </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiameti ja Kaitsepolitseiameti juht v&otilde;ib temale alluva politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada v&auml;ljaspool tema teenistuspiirkonda ja -&uuml;lesandeid k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 27 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>The head of the Police Board or Security Police Board may require a police officer subordinate to him or her to work outside of the service area and beyond the duties of the police officer in the cases provided for in subsection 27 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiteenistusega seotud piirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions in connection with police service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnik ei v&otilde;i: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A police officer shall not: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;tada teise t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures, v&auml;lja arvatud pedagoogilisel, teaduslikul v&otilde;i loomingulisel t&ouml;&ouml;l; </eesti>
<inglise>1) work for another employer with the exception of teaching, research or creative work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) olla erakonna liige; </eesti>
<inglise>2) be a member of a political party; </inglise>
<eesti>3) osaleda streikides; </eesti>
<inglise>3) participate in strikes; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kuuluda &auml;ri&uuml;hingu juhtorganisse, kontroll- ega revisjoniorganisse. </eesti>
<inglise>4) be a member of the management body, controlling body or audit body of a company. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) (Kehtetu - 14.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.16.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 28, 167) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) (Repealed - 14.03.2000 entered into force 16.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 28, 167) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiametnikule ei v&auml;ljastata tema politseiteenistusse v&otilde;tmise, teisele ametikohale &uuml;leviimise ja politseiteenistusest vabastamise v&otilde;i temale distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise k&auml;skkirja koopiat, kui k&auml;skkiri sisaldab riigisaladust v&otilde;i muud avalikustamisele mittekuuluvat teavet. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A police officer shall not be issued a copy of the directive on the basis of which the police officer was employed in the police service, transferred to another position or released from the police service, or a copy of a directive imposing a disciplinary punishment on the police officer if such directive contains state secrets or any other information which is not subject to disclosure. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellisel juhul v&auml;ljastatakse talle v&auml;ljav&otilde;te k&auml;skkirjast, millest on v&auml;lja j&auml;etud riigisaladust sisaldav teave. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the police officer shall be issued an extract of the directive which does not contain information on state secrets. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Politseiametnik ei v&otilde;i kolme aasta jooksul p&auml;rast politseiteenistusest vabastamist t&ouml;&ouml;tada turvateenuseid v&otilde;i eradetektiiviteenuseid osutavates era&otilde;iguslikes juriidilistes isikutes. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Within three years after release from the police service, a police officer shall not work for legal persons in private law which provide security services or private detective services. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;tamine variisikuna </eesti>
<inglise>Police officers acting as undercover agents </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku t&ouml;&ouml;tamine variisikuna (j&auml;litustegevuse seaduse &sect; 7 punkt 9) ei too kaasa tema politseiteenistussuhte peatamist ega vabastamist politseiametniku ametikohalt ning tema poolt variisikuna t&auml;idetavad &uuml;lesanded loetakse politseile pandud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>If a police officer acts as an undercover agent (pursuant to clause 7 9) of the Surveillance Act), his or her service relationship in the police service shall not be suspended or he or she shall not be released from the position of police officer; the duties performed by the police officer in the capacity of an undercover agent are deemed to be performance of the duties of a police officer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolituskulude h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Reimbursement of training expenses </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnik, politseikadett ja politsei&otilde;ppeasutuse l&otilde;petanu on kohustatud h&uuml;vitama riigi poolt tema koolitamisele v&otilde;i v&auml;lisriigis korraldatud t&auml;iendus&otilde;ppele tehtud otsesed kulutused, kui ta: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A police officer, cadet or police training institution graduate shall compensate for the direct expenses incurred by the state for his or her training or in-service training organised in a foreign state if he or she: </inglise>
<eesti>1) katkestas m&otilde;juva p&otilde;hjuseta &otilde;pingud v&otilde;i t&auml;iendus&otilde;ppe; </eesti>
<inglise>1) interrupts the studies or in-service training without good reason; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vabastati politseiteenistusest s&uuml;&uuml;dim&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) is released from the police service upon the entry into force of a conviction by a court; </inglise>
<eesti>3) vabastati politseiteenistusest distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest; </eesti>
<inglise>3) is released from the police service for a disciplinary offence; </inglise>
<eesti>4) vabastati politseiteenistusest oma algatusel; </eesti>
<inglise>4) is released from the police service on his or her own initiative; </inglise>
<eesti>5) arvati v&auml;lja politsei&otilde;ppeasutusest &otilde;ppet&ouml;&ouml;st mahaj&auml;&auml;muse v&otilde;i mitterahuldava &otilde;ppeedukuse t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;i distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest; </eesti>
<inglise>5) is expelled from a police training institution due backlog in studies or non-satisfactory performance or for a disciplinary offence; </inglise>
<eesti>6) keeldub p&auml;rast kooli l&otilde;petamist politseiteenistusse asumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>6) after graduating, refuses to assume police service. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koolitus- ja t&auml;iendus&otilde;ppe kulusid ei pea h&uuml;vitama politseiametnik, kes: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Training and in-service-training expenses shall not be compensated for by a police officer who: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&auml;rast &otilde;ppeasutuse l&otilde;petamist v&otilde;i t&auml;iendus&otilde;ppe l&auml;bimist on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud politseis ajavahemiku, mis on v&otilde;rdne poolteisekordse koolitusajaga, kuid mitte v&auml;hem kui kolm aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) after graduation from a training institution or completion of in-service training has worked in the police during a period of time which equals the duration of the training period multiplied by 1.5 but for not less than three years; </inglise>
<eesti>2) on teenistusest vabastatud oma algatusel seoses p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse v&otilde;i vajadusega hooldada p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse v&otilde;i puudega perekonnaliiget. </eesti>
<inglise>2) is released from the police service on his or her own initiative due to his or her permanent incapacity for work or a need to care for a family member with permanent incapacity for work or disability. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Koolitus- ja t&auml;iendus&otilde;ppe kulude arvestamise korra kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for calculating training and in-service training expenses shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku atesteerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Evaluation of Police Officers </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku atesteerimise &uuml;ldine kord </eesti>
<inglise>General procedure for evaluation of police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnik kuulub atesteerimisele &uuml;ks kord kolme aasta jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Police officers shall be evaluated once every three years. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametnike atesteerimise korra ja atesteerimislehe vormi kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for evaluation of police officers and the form of an evaluation record shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Atesteerimistulemused kantakse atesteerimislehele ja politseiametniku teenistuslehele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Evaluation results shall be entered in the evaluation record and the service record of a police officer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametnike atesteerimise n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Evaluation requirements of police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnike p&otilde;higruppide atesteerimise n&otilde;uded kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The evaluation requirements for the basic categories of police officers shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametnike atesteerimise n&otilde;uded kehtestab siseminister v&otilde;i tema poolt volitatud ulatuses Politseiameti ja Kaitsepolitseiameti juht koosk&otilde;lastatult Siseministeeriumi konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoniga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The evaluation requirements of police officers shall be established by the Minister of Internal Affairs or by the head of the Police Board or Security Police Board to the extent authorised by the Minister of Internal Affairs in agreement with the competition and evaluation committee of the Ministry of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Atesteerimisn&otilde;uded peavad olema politseiametnikule tema teenistuskohas k&auml;ttesaadavad. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The evaluation requirements shall be accessible by a police officer in his or her place of service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon </eesti>
<inglise>Competition and evaluation committee of police officers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnike kandidaatide hindamist konkursil ning politseiametnike atesteerimist teostavad Siseministeeriumi konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon ning politseiametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The competition and evaluation committee of the Ministry of Internal Affairs and competition and evaluation committees of police officers shall perform the assessment of candidates for the position of police officer by a competition and the evaluation of police officers. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonide moodustamise korra ja p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for establishing competition and evaluation committees and the statutes of the competition and evaluation committees shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku ergutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Incentives for Police Officers </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Ergutused </eesti>
<inglise>Incentives </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseinikule kohaldatavad ergutused on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The incentives applied in respect of police officers are the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&auml;nu avaldamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) expression of thanks; </inglise>
<eesti>2) rahalise preemia andmine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) granting of a monetary award; </inglise>
<eesti>3) hinnalise kingituse andmine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) giving of a valuable gift; </inglise>
<eesti>4) autasustamine aukirjaga; </eesti>
<inglise>4) award of a certificate of honour; </inglise>
<eesti>5) autasustamine nimelise relvaga; </eesti>
<inglise>5) award of a weapon registered to the name of the police officer; </inglise>
<eesti>6) autasustamine politsei teeneteristiga. </eesti>
<inglise>6) award of a police cross of merit. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politsei teeneteristi liigid ja kirjelduse, teeneteristiga autasustamise tingimused ning teeneteristi kandmise korra kehtestab siseminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The types and description of a police cross of merit, the conditions for award of a cross of merit and the procedure for wearing a cross of merit shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Silmapaistvate teenete eest v&otilde;ib erandkorras k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud ergutusi kohaldada ka nende isikute autasustamisel, kes ei ole politseiametnikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) As an exception, the incentives provided for in subsection (1) of this section may also be applied as an award for outstanding merits in respect of persons who are not police officers. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Ergutuse kohaldamise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Grounds for application of incentives </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnikule v&otilde;ib ergutust kohaldada: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An incentive may be applied in respect of a police officer for the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kauaaegse laitmatu teenistuse v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>1) a long-term excellent service; or </inglise>
<eesti>2) teenistuskohustuste silmapaistvalt hea t&auml;itmise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>2) noteworthy performance of duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;heaegselt v&otilde;ib kohaldada mitut ergutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Several incentives may be applied simultaneously. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Ergutuse kohaldamise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Authority to apply incentive </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnikule ergutuse kohaldamise &otilde;igus on isikul, kellel on selle politseiametniku ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The authority to apply an incentive lies with the person authorised to appoint a given police officer to office. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Siseministril on &otilde;igus kohaldada ergutusi k&otilde;igile politseiametnikele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Internal Affairs has the authority to apply incentives in respect of all police officers. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiameti ja Kaitsepolitseiameti juhil on &otilde;igus kohaldada ergutusi k&otilde;igile talle alluvatele politseiametnikele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Head of the Police Board and the Head of the Security Police Board have the authority to apply incentives in respect of all police officers subordinate to them. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 39 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 5 ja 6 nimetatud ergutuste kohaldamise &otilde;igus on ainult siseministril. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Only the Minister of Internal Affairs has the authority to apply the incentives specified in clauses 39 (1) 5) and 6). </inglise>
<eesti>9. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 9 </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku distsiplinaarvastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary Liability of Police Officers </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristused </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary punishments </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametnikule m&auml;&auml;ratavad distsiplinaarkaristused on: </eesti>
<inglise>The disciplinary punishments imposed on police officers are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) noomitus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) reprimand; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ametipalga v&auml;hendamine 10-50 protsenti kuni kolmeks kuuks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) reduction of salary by 10 to 50 per cent for up to three months; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teenistusest vabastamine avaliku teenistuse seaduse &sect; 118 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>3) release from the service pursuant to &sect; 118 of the Public Service Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise alus </eesti>
<inglise>Grounds for imposing disciplinary punishments </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnikule v&otilde;ib distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;rata distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A disciplinary punishment may be imposed on a police officer for a disciplinary offence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Iga distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata ainult &uuml;he distsiplinaarkaristuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Only one disciplinary punishment may be imposed for each disciplinary offence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Authority to impose disciplinary punishment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 42 punktides 1 ja 2 nimetatud distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus on asutuse juhil ning punktis 3 nimetatud distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus on politseiametniku ametikohale nimetamise &otilde;igust omaval asutuse juhil. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The head of a body has the authority to impose disciplinary penalties specified in clauses 42 1) and 2) and the head of a body who has the authority to appoint the police officer to office has the authority to impose a disciplinary penalty specified in clause 42 3) of this Act </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Siseministril on &otilde;igus distsiplinaarkaristus m&auml;&auml;rata k&otilde;igile politseiametnikele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Internal Affairs has the authority to impose a disciplinary punishment on any police officer. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiameti juhil on &otilde;igus distsiplinaarkaristus m&auml;&auml;rata k&otilde;igile talle alluvatele politseiametnikele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The head of the Police Board has the authority to impose a disciplinary punishment on any police officer subordinate to him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Siseministril on &otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;rata Politseiameti ja Kaitsepolitseiameti juhile k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 42 punktides 1 ja 2 nimetatud distsiplinaarkaristusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Minister of Internal Affairs has the authority to impose a disciplinary punishment specified in clauses 42 1) and 2) of this Act on the head of the Police Board or head of the Security Police Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Politseiameti ja Kaitsepolitseiameti juhil on &otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;rata temale alluvale politseiametnikule, kes on ametisse nimetatud siseministri poolt, k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 42 punktides 1 ja 2 nimetatud distsiplinaarkaristusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The head of the Police Board and the head of the Security Police Board have the authority to impose a disciplinary punishment specified in clause 42 1) or 2) of this Act on any police officer subordinate to him or her who has been appointed to office by the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarjuurdlus </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary investigation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo ja selle toimepannud isiku kindlakstegemiseks viiakse l&auml;bi distsiplinaarjuurdlus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A disciplinary investigation shall be conducted to ascertain whether a disciplinary offence was committed and to determine the person who committed it. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Distsiplinaarjuurdluse algatamise &otilde;igus alluvate politseiametnike suhtes on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The authority to commence a disciplinary investigation concerning subordinate police officers lies with: </inglise>
<eesti>1) siseministril; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the Minister of Internal Affairs; </inglise>
<eesti>2) Politseiameti juhil; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the head of the Police Board; </inglise>
<eesti>3) asutuse juhil. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the head of a body. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Distsiplinaarjuurdlus algatatakse k&auml;skkirjaga, milles m&auml;&auml;ratakse distsiplinaarjuurdluse l&auml;biviija ja l&auml;biviimise t&auml;htaeg. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A disciplinary investigation is commenced by a directive whereby the investigator and term for the disciplinary investigation are determined. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;skkiri tehakse viivitamata teatavaks politseiametnikule, kelle suhtes distsiplinaarjuurdlus algatati. </eesti>
<inglise>The police officer against whom a disciplinary investigation is commenced shall be notified of the directive promptly. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Distsiplinaarjuurdluse l&auml;biviija v&otilde;ib distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo kohta n&otilde;uda seletusi ja koguda t&otilde;endeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The investigator of a disciplinary investigation may request explanations about and gather evidence on the disciplinary offence. </inglise>
<eesti>Seletuse n&otilde;udmine politseiametnikult, kelle suhtes distsiplinaarjuurdlus algatati, on kohustuslik. </eesti>
<inglise>It is mandatory to request the explanation of a police officer against whom the disciplinary investigation is commenced. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Distsiplinaarjuurdluse l&otilde;puleviimisel koostab selle l&auml;biviija distsiplinaarjuurdluse kokkuv&otilde;tte, milles distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo ja selle toimepannud isiku kindlakstegemisel m&auml;rgitakse v&auml;hemalt allj&auml;rgnev: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon conclusion of a disciplinary investigation, the investigator shall prepare a summary of the disciplinary investigation which, if the commission of the disciplinary offence is ascertained and the person who committed it is determined, shall set out at least the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo toimepannud politseiametniku ees- ja perekonnanimi ning ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the given name, surname and position of the police officer who committed the disciplinary offence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo kirjeldus ning toimepanemise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a description and the time and place of the disciplinary offence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo toimepanemist kinnitavad t&otilde;endid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) evidence in favour of the commission of the disciplinary offence; </inglise>
<eesti>4) viide distsiplinaarvastutust s&auml;testavale seadusele ja selle s&auml;ttele, mida politseiametnik kirjeldatud teoga rikkus. </eesti>
<inglise>4) reference to the Act providing for disciplinary liability and to the provision which the police officer violated by his or her act. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Distsiplinaarjuurdluse kokkuv&otilde;te allkirjastatakse distsiplinaarjuurdluse l&auml;biviija poolt, esitatakse viivitamatult distsiplinaarjuurdluse algatanud isikule ja seda tutvustatakse isikule, kelle suhtes distsiplinaarjuurdlus l&auml;bi viidi. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The summary of a disciplinary investigation shall be signed by the investigator of the disciplinary offence, forwarded promptly to the person who initiated the disciplinary investigation and introduced to the person against whom the disciplinary investigation was conducted. </inglise>
<eesti>10. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 10 </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiteenistusest vabastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Release from Police Service </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiteenistusest vabastamise &uuml;ldine kord </eesti>
<inglise>General procedure for release from police service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lisaks avaliku teenistuse seaduses s&auml;testatud teenistusest vabastamise alustele vabastatakse politseiametnik politseiteenistusest k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 47 ja 49 s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In addition to the grounds for release from the service provided for in the Public Service Act, a police officer shall be released from the police service on the bases of and pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect;&sect; 47 and 49 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametniku v&otilde;ib politseiteenistusest vabastada isik, kellel on tema teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A police officer may be released from the police service by a person authorised to employ him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. (Kehtetu - 11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. (Repealed -11,100, 2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiprefektuuri juhi ja Kaitsepolitseiameti regionaalse struktuuri&uuml;ksuse juhi ametist vabastamine teenistust&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumise t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release of head of police prefecture and head of regional unit of Security Police Board from office due to expiry of term of service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiprefektuuri juht ja Kaitsepolitseiameti regionaalse struktuuri&uuml;ksuse juht vabastatakse ametist teenistust&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumise t&otilde;ttu ning nimetatakse vastavalt Politseiameti juhi ja Kaitsepolitseiameti juhi poolt muule k&otilde;rgema politseiametniku ametikohale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The head of a police prefecture and the head of a regional unit of the Security Police Board shall be released from office due to the expiry of their term of office and shall be appointed to another position of higher police officer by the head of the Police Board or head of the Security Police Board, as appropriate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiprefektuuri juhi v&otilde;i Kaitsepolitseiameti regionaalse struktuuri&uuml;ksuse juhi v&otilde;ib uueks ametiajaks ametisse tagasi nimetada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The head of a police prefecture and head of a regional unit of the Security Police Board may be re-appointed for a new term of office. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiprefektuuri juhi v&otilde;i Kaitsepolitseiameti regionaalse struktuuri&uuml;ksuse juhi v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud ametikohale nimetada v&otilde;i ametisse tagasi nimetada tema kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The head of a police prefecture and the head of a regional unit of the Security Police Board may be appointed to the position provided for in subsection (1) of this section or re-appointed with the written consent of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui politseiprefektuuri juht v&otilde;i Kaitsepolitseiameti regionaalse struktuuri&uuml;ksuse juht ei ole n&otilde;us k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud ametikohale v&otilde;i ametisse tagasi nimetamisega ning kui ta ei soovi enda nimetamist muule politseiametniku ametikohale, vabastatakse ta politseiteenistusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The head of a police prefecture or head of a regional unit of the Security Police Board shall be released from the police service if he or she does not consent to his or her appointment to the position provided for in subsection (1) of this section or to his or her re-appointment to office, and does not wish to be appointed to any other position of police officer. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui puudub k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud nimetamiseks vajalik vaba ametikoht ning politseiprefektuuri juht v&otilde;i Kaitsepolitseiameti regionaalse struktuuri&uuml;ksuse juht ei ole n&otilde;us nimetamisega muule politseiamentiku vabale ametikohale, siis vabastatakse ta politseiteenistusest ning talle makstakse h&uuml;vitist kuue kuu ametipalga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If there is no vacant position necessary for the appointment specified in subsection (1) of this section and the head of a police prefecture or head of a regional unit of the Security Police Board does not consent to being appointed to another vacant position of police officer, he or she shall be released from the police service and shall receive compensation in an amount equal to his or her six months' salary. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiteenistusest vabastamine piirvanuse t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release from police service due to reaching of specified age limit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnik v&otilde;ib olla politseiteenistuses kuni j&auml;rgmise piirvanuseni: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A police officer may be accepted for police service until he or she reaches the following age limits: </inglise>
<eesti>1) noorem- ja vanempolitseiametnikuna - kuni 55-aastaseks saamiseni; </eesti>
<inglise>1) as a junior or senior police officer - until the age of 55 years; </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&otilde;rgema politseiametnikuna - kuni 60-aastaseks saamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>2) as a higher police officer - until the age of 60 years. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametnik vabastatakse politseiteenistusest k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 m&auml;rgitud piirvanuse t&auml;itumisele j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A police officer shall be released from the police service on the first working day of the month following the month of attaining the specified age limit set out in (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Politseiametnik v&otilde;ib olla politseiteenistuses kuni riikliku pensionikindlustuse seaduse &sect;-s 7 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioniea saabumiseni Politseiameti v&otilde;i Kaitsepolitseiameti juhi loal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) With the permission of the head of the Police Board or head of the Security Police Board, a police officer may be employed in the police service until he or she attains the pensionable age provided for in &sect; 7 of the State Pension Insurance Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud politseiametnik vabastatakse riikliku pensionikindlustuse seaduse &sect;-s 7 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioniea saabumisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A police officer specified in subsection (3) of this section shall be released from the police service when he or she attains the pensionable age provided for in &sect; 7 of the State Pension Insurance Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>11. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 11 </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;pps&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Final Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>Uute palgam&auml;&auml;rade rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of new salary rates </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnike uutele palgam&auml;&auml;radele &uuml;lemineku korra, etapid ja t&auml;htajad kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The procedure for and the stages and terms of transition to new salary rates of police officers shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;leminek uutele palgam&auml;&auml;radele peab olema l&otilde;petatud 2000. aasta 1. jaanuariks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The transition to new salary rates shall be completed by 1 January 2000. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&uuml;mne aasta jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest, v&otilde;ib Vabariigi Valitsus suurendada m&otilde;nes piirkonnas t&ouml;&ouml;tavate politseiametnike palka kuni neljandiku v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Within a period of ten years as of the entry into force of this Act, the Government of the Republic may increase the salary of police officers working in certain districts by up to 25 per cent. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 j&otilde;ustub 1998. aasta 1. septembril. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Section 7 of this Act enters into force on 1 September 1998. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Politseiametnike atesteerimine vastavuses k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel kehtestatud atesteerimisn&otilde;uetega peab olema l&otilde;petatud hiljemalt 2002. aasta 31. detsembriks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The evaluation of police officers pursuant to the evaluation requirements established by this Act shall be completed by not later than 31 December 2002. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 08.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 10 s&auml;testatud politseivannet ei pea andma politseiametnik, kes on andnud seni kehtiva politseivande enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A police officer who has taken the police oath valid before the entry into force of this Act is not required to take the police oath provided for in &sect; 10 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist juhtivpolitseiametnikuna t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aeg arvatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisel k&otilde;rgema politseiametnikuna t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aja hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The time of having worked as a leading police officer prior to the entry into force of this Act shall be included in the time of working as a higher police officer upon the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Vormiriietuse kirjelduse ja vormiriietuse esemete kandmise t&auml;htajad kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus m&auml;&auml;rusega kolme kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The description of and the terms for wearing police clothing items shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic within three months after the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Isikul, kes on politseiteenistusest vabastatud p&auml;rast 1991. aasta 1. m&auml;rtsi ja kes saab riiklikku pensioni, on &otilde;igus kuni 2003. aasta 1. jaanuarini esitada taotlus pensioni &uuml;mberarvutamiseks politseiametniku pensioniks, kui ta vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 21 (1) s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A person who has been released from police service before 1 March 1991 and who receives state pension has the right to submit, before 1 January 2003, an application for the recalculation of his or her pension to receive a pension for police officers provided that such person complies with the conditions provided for in &sect; 21 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Isikul, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tab politseiametniku ametikohal ja saab riiklikku pensioni, on &otilde;igus kuni 2003. aasta 1. jaanuarini esitada taotlus pensioni &uuml;mberarvutamiseks politseiametniku pensioniks, kui ta vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 21 (1) s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A person who is working in the position of a police officer and who receives state pension has the right to submit, before 1 January 2003, an application for the recalculation of his or her pension to receive a pension for police officers provided that such person complies with the conditions provided for in &sect; 21 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>(8) P&otilde;hjendatud taotluse korral arvutatakse varem m&auml;&auml;ratud riiklik pension &uuml;mber politseiametniku pensioniks taotluse esitamisele j&auml;rgneva kuu 1. kuup&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) If the application is justified, the state pension granted earlier shall be recalculated as a pension for police officers as of the first day of the month following the submission of the application. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui isik j&auml;tkab teenistust politseiametnikuna, arvutatakse tema riiklik pension &uuml;mber politseiametniku pensioniks alates tema politseiteenistusest vabastamisele j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>If a person continues to serve as a police officer, his or her state pension shall be recalculated as a pension for police officers as of the date following the date of his or her release from police service. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 85, 511) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>Siseministeeriumi k&otilde;rgema v&otilde;i vanemametniku ametikohale nimetatud politseiametniku tagatised </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantees for police officers appointed to position of higher or senior official of Ministry of Infernal Affairs </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiametnikule, kes on vabastatud politseiteenistusest seoses tema nimetamisega Siseministeeriumi k&otilde;rgema v&otilde;i vanemametniku ametikohale: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A police officer who is released from the police service in connection with his or her appointment to the position of higher or senior official of the Ministry of Internal Affairs shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) s&auml;ilitatakse tema soovil politseiametniku ametipalk; </eesti>
<inglise>1) continue to receive the salary of a police officer if he or she so wishes; </inglise>
<eesti>2) s&auml;ilitatakse &otilde;igus kasutada senise t&ouml;&ouml;andja eluruumi. </eesti>
<inglise>2) retain the right to use the housing provided by the former employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud isik on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud Siseministeeriumi k&otilde;rgema ja vanemametniku ametikohal v&auml;hemalt kaks aastat, v&otilde;ib siseminister ta tema soovil politseiametnikuks tagasi nimetada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the person specified in subsection (1) of this section has worked in the position of higher or senior official of the Ministry of Internal Affairs for at least two years, the Minister of Internal Affairs may reappoint him or her as a police officer at his or her request. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiametniku vaba ametikoha olemasolu korral ei v&otilde;i siseminister tema ametisse tagasinimetamisest keelduda. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Internal Affairs shall not refuse to appoint such person to office if a vacant position of police officer exists. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teenistusaeg Siseministeeriumi k&otilde;rgema ja vanemametniku ametikohal arvatakse selle ametikoha teenistusaja hulka, kus politseiametnik t&ouml;&ouml;tas enne Siseministeeriumi k&otilde;rgema ja vanemametniku ametikohale nimetamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The period of service in the position of higher or senior official of the Ministry of Internal Affairs shall be included in the period of service of such position in which the police officer worked prior to his or her appointment to the position of higher or senior official of the Ministry of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 3 nimetatud tagatised kehtivad selles l&otilde;ikes nimetatud isiku suhtes seni, kuni ei ole katkenud tema teenistusaeg Siseministeeriumi k&otilde;rgema ja vanemametniku ametikohal. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The guarantees specified in subsections (1) and (3) of this section shall apply to the persons specified in the corresponding subsections until the period of service in the position of higher or senior official of the Ministry of Internal Affairs has not been suspended. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud tagatis laieneb k&otilde;rgematele ja vanempolitseiametnikele, kes olid politseiteenistusest vabastatud seoses nimetamisega Siseministeeriumi k&otilde;rgema ametniku ametikohale enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The guarantee specified in subsection (3) of this section extends to such higher or senior police officers who were released from the police service in connection with their appointment to the position of higher or senior official of the Ministry of Internal Affairs prior to the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
